HEADWORD: Hornstone
<hw>Horn"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A siliceous stone, a variety of quartz, closely resembling flint,
but more brittle; -- called also <altname>chert</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

